[b]Commodity Pulse Matrix v3[/b] is a multi-timeframe confluence indicator for commodities. It evaluates each bar across six analytical categories — Flow, Momentum, Trend, Volatility, Structure, and Divergence — and aggregates the results into a scored matrix table directly on the chart.

[b]What it does[/b]

Instead of reading several indicators separately, the matrix gives you a single view of setup quality across timeframes. Each category produces a directional score; these combine into an overall Heat Score (0–1) that reflects how aligned conditions are at any given moment.

[b]Categories[/b]

[list]
[*][b]Flow[/b] — Directional bias from price and volume movement
[*][b]Momentum[/b] — Short-term momentum strength and direction
[*][b]Trend[/b] — Medium-to-long-term trend alignment across timeframes
[*][b]Volatility[/b] — ATR expansion vs. contraction — whether conditions favor trending or ranging behavior
[*][b]Structure[/b] — Market structure events: Break of Structure (BOS) and Change of Character (CHoCH)
[*][b]Divergence[/b] — Momentum-price divergences as early reversal signals
[/list]

[b]Entry system[/b]

Three entry types are available independently: breakouts, pullbacks to support/resistance, and trend continuations after mini-pullbacks. A configurable signal quality gate filters out entries during low-volume or range-bound conditions. Counter-trend entries are also supported with a higher momentum threshold.

[b]Risk management[/b]

Stop-loss and take-profit levels are ATR-based. Take-profit has four modes: Simple, Smart (ATR + swing structure), Conservative, and Multi-Target (three levels).

[b]Table display[/b]

Two modes:
[list]
[*][b]Full[/b] — All timeframe scores plus individual Flow, Momentum, Trend, and Divergence detail rows
[*][b]Compact[/b] — Core timeframe scores only, suited for smaller screens
[/list]

